Ever catch your baby staring at the monitor? 👀

The little red and green lights on baby monitors are very distracting and can cause middle of the night disruptions! It’s hard not to stare at these lights in the middle of the night! 👀

Your baby will cycle to a more active state every 3-4 hours overnight with the potential to wake up especially if they see a light!

PRO TIP👉 Cover them up with a small piece of painter’s tape! 

➕Baby monitors should also be secured to a wall or on another piece of furniture away from the crib.
